Mildred Grieveson ( b. October 10 , 1946 in England ) is a popular British author of over 160 romance novels as Anne Mather . She also write as Caroline Fleming and Cardine Fleming . Mildred Grieveson began to write down stories in her childhood years . The first novel that she actually finished , Caroline , was also her first book to be published . Her novel , Leopard in the Snow , was developed into a 1978 movie . Mildred Grieveson born October 10 , 1946 in England . She had written all through her infant and junior years and on into her teens , the stories changing from children 's adventures to torrid gypsy passions . Her mother used to gather these up from time to time , when her bedroom became too untidy , and disposed of them ! . Mildred married young and became a housewife , her husband suggested that she ought to send one of her stories to a publisher . Mildred always wanted to write , and for years she wrote only for her own pleasure . The trouble was , she never used to finish any of the stories , and Caroline , her first published book , was the first book she had actually completed . She was newly married then , and her daughter was just a baby , and she had quite a job juggling her household chores and scribbling away in exercise books every chance she got . She now has two grown - up children , a son and daughter , and two adorable grandchildren , Abigail and Ben . 